This "coupler":
http://www.thebusstop.com.au/busstore/products/16/122/gearbox_coupler_68-79/
 can be bad, and you won't notice it by looking at it. Remove it from the
vehicle
 and insure that the "round" part does not rotate independently of the
"cage" part.
This mode of failure will cause the symptoms you describe.
The result of poorly made aftermarket crap.
